## About me

Now I am a PhD candidate in geophysics in the [Department of Earth and Planetary Science](http://www.mcgill.ca/eps/) at [McGill University](http://www.mcgill.ca/) since 2014. I received my BSc degree in geophysics from [University of Science and Technology of China](http://en.ustc.edu.cn) in July 2014. Currently, Iâ€™m working with my supervisor [Prof. Yajing Liu](mailto:yajing.liu@mcgill.ca) in [McGill Earthquake Process Group](http://eps.mcgill.ca/~crowe/EQprocesses/).

My research interest mainly focus on:
1. Stress drops of fluid induced seismicity in West Canadian Sedimentary Basin(WCSB) area;
2. Upper crustal structures near the Leech River Fault area on southern Vancouver Island area and potential hazard implications.

## Education Background
- Ph.D. candidate, Department of Earth and Planetary Science,  McGill University, 09/2014 - present
